data.name: quaSoulToggle.ToolTip
data.value: All spells have a chance to trigger the Soul Search effect on hit, revealing enemy details. Also replaces the vanilla Soul Search 'magnifying glass' icon with a more compact one, since you'll be seeing it a lot.

data.name: quaAccuracyToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Normalizes accuracy values. This does not mean no misses, but instead the normal Agi-based hit rate of most spells. Status spells: Changes positive/negative status effects' accuracy to 100. All spells: Changes all spells' accuracy to 100 (Also includes Escape, Extinction, etc.)

data.name: expFilenameLabel.ToolTip
data.value: IPS patch filename. Default is 'merrowpatch_(seed number)' if nothing is typed. Export will automatically overwrite any existing file with the same name, and will open a window to the save location. It will also create a 'filename + Spoiler.txt' file in the same directory that lists patch contents, seed, and other information.

data.name: newLabel.Text
data.value:
● Added Fast Monastery option, allowing the player to quickly exit the Monastery at the start.
● Overhauled interface arrangement for Quest patch creation.
● Overhauled item randomization selection to add Gifters and Wingsmiths options, and granular selection controls.

data.name: rndChestToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Change the contents of all chests. SHUFFLED: All default chest contents are shuffled among all chests. RANDOM: Chests are randomized to contain any standard item. RANDOM&WINGS: Chests are randomized to contain any standard item or wing. RANDOM&GEMS: Chests are randomized to contain any standard item or Elemental Gem. CHAOS: Chests are randomized to contain any standard item, wing, or Elemental Gem. WINGS: Chests are randomized to contain any wing. GEMS: Chests are randomized to contain any Elemental Gem. WINGS&GEMS: Chests are randomized to contain any wing or Elemental Gem. CUSTOM: Chests are randomized as selected below. [WARNING - Including gems or wings can cause sequence breaks.]

data.name: rndDropsToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Change the items dropped by non-Boss enemies. All Random options exclude blanks. SHUFFLED: All default item drops are shuffled among all enemies, including blanks. RANDOM: Drops are randomized to contain any standard item. RANDOM&WINGS: Drops are randomized to contain any standard item or wing. RANDOM&GEMS: Drops are randomized to contain any standard item or Elemental Gem. CHAOS: Drops are randomized to contain any standard item, wing, or Elemental Gem. WINGS: Drops are randomized to contain any wing. GEMS: Drops are randomized to contain any Elemental Gem. WINGS&GEMS: Drops are randomized to contain any wing or Elemental Gem. CUSTOM: Drops are randomized as selected below. [WARNING - Including gems or wings can cause sequence breaks.]

data.name: rndGiftersToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Change the items granted by item-gifting NPCs. All Random options exclude Shannon. SHUFFLED: All default gift items are shuffled among all gift NPCs. (Includes Shannon.) STANDARD: Gifts are randomized to be any standard item. STANDARD&WINGS: Gifts are randomized to be any standard item or wing. STANDARD&GEMS: Gifts are randomized to be any standard item or Elemental Gem. CHAOS: Gifts are randomized to be any standard item, wing, or Elemental Gem. WINGS: Gifts are randomized to be any wing. GEMS: Gifts are randomized to be any Elemental Gem. WINGS&GEMS: Gifts are randomized to be any wing or Elemental Gem. CUSTOM: Gifts are randomized as set in the below menu. [WARNING - Including gems or wings can cause sequence breaks.]

data.name: rndWingsmithsToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Change the items granted by Wingsmith NPCs. SHUFFLED: All wings are shuffled among all wingsmith NPCs. STANDARD: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any standard item. STANDARD&WINGS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any standard item or wing. STANDARD&GEMS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any standard item or Elemental Gem. CHAOS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any standard item, wing, or Elemental Gem. WINGS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any wing. GEMS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any Elemental Gem. WINGS&GEMS: Wingsmith items are randomized to be any wing or Elemental Gem. CUSTOM: Wingsmith items are randomized as set in the below menu. [WARNING - Any of these options can cause sequence breaks.]

data.name: rndSpellToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Change the properties of all spells as discrete units, except for unlock level and menu positioning. SHUFFLED: Redistribute spell properties randomly, with some crash protection rules. <SPELL>: Set all spells to use the specified spell's properties. No crash protection.

data.name: rndSpellNamesToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Spell names are updated to be a prefix/suffix combination based on the original and modifier spell. Ambiguous: Hinted spell names will randomly select whether original or modifier provide prefix or suffix. Obvious: Hinted spell names will always be in the format (original prefix, modifier suffix).

data.name: quaMonsterScaleToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Scales enemy stats by simple multiplication. Applies to bosses. NOTE: The 'Enemy stat scaling' feature is applied AFTER the effects of 'Randomize monster stats'. Setting both to higher values may cause extreme results.

data.name: rndMonsterStatsToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Randomizes monster stats within regions. All monsters in each region will receive new stats, randomly chosen from a range from lowest to highest local vanilla values for that stat. Increasing the Variance modifier will increase the width of that range, beyond the vanilla lowest-highest bounds. Repeat for all stats. Example: at Variance 1.0, all Holy Plain enemies will get a new random HP value between 9HP (Were Hare HP) and 28HP (Big Mouth HP). Does not apply to bosses. NOTE: The 'Enemy stat scaling' feature is applied AFTER randomization and Variance. Setting both values higher may have extreme results.

data.name: rndTextPaletteToggle.ToolTip
data.value: Changes the text colour palette. <COLOUR>: Use one of four default included colours. SHUFFLED: Select one of those four included colours at random. RANDOM: Generate a palette at random. [Feature unfinished, quality not guaranteed.]

data.name: advHelpLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
This is a generic IPS patch generator. Handy for quick hacks and tests, it will generate a clean IPS patch for whatever use you may need. Enter the PATCH CONTENT you want to write (in hexadecimal 2-character bytes), and the ADDRESS to start writing at (as a 6-character hex string).
Always make backups of your files before patching. This tool will generate properly formatted patches, but it is your responsibility to know what you are patching and why. Merrow is offered without warranty: please refer to the license readme file for more info.

data.name: binHelpLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
This is a binary file data extractor. Handy for quick reference and grabbing bulk info, it will read the input file at specified locations and fetch the specified values, and optionally, create a text file containing the read bytes in hexadecimal format.
Populate the EXTRACTION LIST with as many entries as needed, in comma-separated hexadecimal or decimal strings in the following format: (Byte_Address,Byte_Length) with no brackets and another comma before the next entry. Ensure you specify whether all addresses/lengths are written as hexadecimal or decimal, using the lower left options. If you would like the exported data to be output to file, check the box at the bottom.
This tool can currently only access values in the following ranges: Address: 000000-FFFFFF (DEC: 0-16777215) Length: 0000-FFFF (DEC: 0-65535) If the ranges are too restrictive for your uses, please get in touch. This is a first attempt but it can be adjusted in future versions.
This tool is as restrictive as possible, to prevent possible memory errors and other problems, but it is experimental software. It is your responsibility to know what you are reading from files, and why. Merrow is offered without warranty: please refer to the license readme file for more info.

data.name: binExtractLabel.ToolTip
data.value: Enter comma-separated hexadecimal or decimal values in this field. Each entry should follow this format: (address),(length),... The binary file will be read starting at [address], for [length] bytes. After entry, ensure you select below what format each value type is in.

data.name: crcHelpLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
This is a CRC (N64 file checksum) Repair Tool. The checksum is a value calculated based on a certain portion of a Z64 file, that is used to verify that the file is legitimate. Making modifications (with tools or patches) to that portion of the file will cause the checksum to be incorrect, which causes certain hardware and emulation to fail on boot.
This tool can be used to recalculate and update the checksum of a Z64 file, allowing hardware to recognize it as legitimate without errors or issues. It uses a DLL compiled from existing checksum calculation code in C. Full details of the algorithm and the license information for the C script are available in the repo, under the CRC64 subfolder.
This tool is restricted to Z64 files, to prevent possible memory errors and other problems, but it is experimental software. Please ensure you back up any files before attempting any checksum repairs. It is your responsibility to know what you are doing to files, and why. Merrow is offered without warranty: please refer to the license readme file for more info.
